# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) to opt into stable local code signing.
#
# The example app is ad-hoc signed by default, so every rebuild gets a new code
# identity and macOS re-prompts for the CEF Keychain ("Chromium Safe Storage")
# and XCTest automation/accessibility every time. Sign with a stable identity
# and those one-time grants persist across rebuilds.
#
# Create the identity once with:  scripts/make-signing-identity.sh
# Then uncomment the line below. scripts/cli.swift forwards it to xcodebuild.
# See documents/code-signing.md.

# CHROMIUMKIT_SIGN_IDENTITY="ChromiumKit Local"
